When you’re stuck in bed with a compressed nerve in your back, @raymond_now brings Christmas to you! Happy Holidays everyone!

When you are a photography-obsessed couple, you get each other film cameras for Christmas. One is the straight-laced Kodak ULTRA F9. And the other is the super quirky Half Frame Kodak EKTAR H35 What are your guesses for which is mine and which is for @raymond_now ?
.
.
.
@kodak #kodak #kodaktrix400 #kodaktrix #trix400 #film #filmphotography #kodakektarh35 #kodakultraf9 #35mm

A few of you guessed it… The Half Frame Kodak EKTAR H35 is mine! All mine! (Except when I let Raymond use it.) I am so excited to load this little cutie up with Tri-X and… well, I’m super duper injured right now but I’ll figure out how to make use of it! @raymond_now is already out with his new Kodak ULTRA F9 and some Tri-X. What are your recommendations for other film stocks to use with these cameras?
.
.
.
@kodak #kodak #kodaktrix400 #kodaktrix #trix400 #film #filmphotography #kodakektarh35 #kodakultraf9 #35mm

As you know, I’ve been stuck in bed for over a month with a back injury. @raymond_now is going to film a video update for you all very soon but, in the meantime, I’m reminiscing about old photo adventures! This was my first time up on the overlook of Grand Prismatic Spring. Those of you that were with me know it was a bit of a hike, but what a view! PS- If you’re looking for a workshop in Yellowstone National Park, @jpons is the guide for you!

It’s sad to think that these photos from our past adventures went unprinted until I received this tiny little printer - the Liene 2x3 Zink Wireless Photo Printer. Of course we’ll still sometimes print larger photos on a larger scale but I’ve been carrying this little printer around with me everywhere. I’ve printed more in the past month than I have in the past year. I adore it! You can learn more about it and get a link to the printer (with a discount code!) In our latest video on YouTube - there’s a link in my IG bio to get there, or you can search YouTube for Leigh & Raymond Photography
.
.
